Giants? send me a tell"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/24/01 11:39:01 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/sigpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ice Comet?</span><hr size=1> It depends on how much the Wizard wants to pay for it. I've seen Ice Comet sell as high as 10k (before the expansions) and as low as 200pp (since the expansions).<br>
<br>
Ice comet is the first truely uber spell Wizards get. It's supposedly our class defining spell until level 60. I think Ice Comet is a decent spell, but it doesn't work in alot of places. Velious is a perfect example. Ice Comet sucks in Velious. It's pretty good for Kunark however.<br>
<br>
Speaking of which, I was hunting in Skyfire tonight and I noticed something really weird. Everytime I nuked a &quot;mature&quot; mob with Ice Comet, I'd either get paritally resisted, or fully resisted. If I hit something a little higher level, like an Old wurm or and Elder Wyvern, it would hit for full every time.<br>
Anyway, the mature mobs were about 8-10 levels below me. The others were only 4-5 levels below me.<br>
Is it possible that VI stealth nerfed resists for low blues? I mean, I could post all of the partials and resists I got on the mature mobs from my logs, and post all the full hits from the higher level mobs, and I'm telling you; I hit for full on higher level mobs all the time. Not a single resist in the three days I've been camping there. The matures resist/partially hit on every single cast.<br>
<br>
 <p><center><br>Jarnin Fisheermann<Br><b>Disciple of Hate<Br><b>Rallos Zek</b><Br></b><Br>Grand Master Fisherman<Br>Master Brewer<Br>Master Chef<Br>Master of Begging<Br><Br><b>DEATH TO AL`KABOR!</b></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umerco81.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merco81</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/25/01 1:39:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ice Comet?</span><hr size=1> That is strange, but I have heard of something like that before. I think some guy using a ice draught in order to help out a newbie with a sandgiant problem got it resisted. I don't know what the exact problem was... but it woulda irritated me. Imagine a high level spell regularly resists the greenies.<br>
